G.3.4.  Refusal Event

   Purpose: Support accountability for AI system "refusal to generate"
   scenarios, interoperable with CAP-SRP draft.

   Extension Identifier: org.ietf.jep.ext.refusal

   Compatibility: wire

   Specification:
   - Adds new event type: $Refuse
   - refusal.reason: Refusal reason classification (e.g.,
     "harmful_content", "out_of_scope", "unable_to_execute")
   - refusal.policy_ref: URI referencing specific policy clause
   - refusal.input_hash: Optional hash of input triggering refusal
   - refusal.evidence: Evidence chain for refusal decision (e.g.,
     classifier outputs)

   Event Format:
   ```json
   {
     "primitive": {
       "type": "REFUSE",
       "payload": {
         "refusal_id": "uuid-refusal-123",
         "reason": "content_safety_violation",
         "policy_ref": "https://example.com/policy/safety/v2#section-3.2",
         "input_hash": {
           "hash": "sha256:3a7bd3e2360a3d29eea436fcfb7e44c7...",
           "alg": "sha256"
         },
         "evidence": [
           {"classifier": "toxicity", "score": 0.98, "threshold": 0.9},
           {"classifier": "bias_detect", "score": 0.85, "threshold": 0.8}
         ],
         "timestamp": 1712345678,
         "actor": "did:example:agent-safety-123"
       }
     }
   }
   ```

   State Machine Integration:
   - $Refuse MAY be executed in ACTIVE or DELEGATED states
   - Post-refusal state options: remain ACTIVE (continue service) or
     TERMINATED (terminate session)
   - Supports responsibility chain tracing: refusal decision can be
     associated with specific agent in authorization chain

   Interoperability with CAP-SRP:
   - refusal.evidence field compatible with CAP-SRP refusal log format
   - MAY carry CAP-SRP "integrity invariants" as evidence
   - refusal.policy_ref supports CAP-SRP policy reference URIs

   Verification Requirements:
   - Verifiers MUST check refusal.reason against deployment policy
   - Verifiers SHOULD validate refusal.evidence cryptographic integrity
   - refusal.input_hash SHOULD match actual input if available

   Privacy Considerations:
   - input_hash enables accountability without exposing raw input
   - evidence SHOULD minimize sensitive data exposure
   - Tier 3 privacy protections apply to refusal evidence

