   }
   ```

   Verification Rules:
   - Post-rotation receipts MUST use new key
   - Pre-rotation receipts remain valid
   - Rotation events MUST be logged in Tier 2

G.4.2.  Enhanced Hardware Binding

   Purpose: Provide physical binding strength comparable to PoP
   (Proof of Personhood), while maintaining compatibility with
   existing TEE binding.

   Extension Identifier: org.ietf.jep.ext.enhanced-hardware

   Compatibility: wire

   Priority: Priority 3 (Security Enhancement) [MAY be upgraded to
   Priority 2 for high-security deployments]

   Specification Enhancement:

   1. Binding Levels:
      - binding_level: "standard" | "enhanced" | "maximum"
        * standard: TEE binding only (existing, Section 5.3)
        * enhanced: TEE + VDF (Verifiable Delay Function)
        * maximum: TEE + VDF + biometric signals

   2. VDF Support (referencing Pietrzak [VDF-PIETRZAK] and
      Wesolowski [VDF-WESOLOWSKI] schemes):
      ```json
      {
        "proof": {
          "signature": "base64-signature",
          "alg": "Ed25519",
          "key_id": "did:example:key1",
          "hardware_proof": {
            "type": "enhanced",
            "binding_level": "enhanced",
            "tee_evidence": {
              // Standard TEE evidence as per Section 5.3.1
            },
            "vdf_proof": {
              "scheme": "pietrzak|wesolowski|class_group",
              "difficulty": 1000000,
              "challenge": "base64-challenge",
              "output": "base64-vdf-output",
              "proof": "base64-vdf-proof",
              "timestamp": 1712345678,
              "source_nonce": "receipt-id-binding",
              "verification_time_ms": 10
            }
          }
        }
      }
      ```

      VDF Requirements:
      - Sequential computation: No parallelization advantage
      - Efficient verification: Verification in polylog(T) time
      - Uniqueness: Exactly one valid output per input
      - Binding: source_nonce MUST bind to specific receipt ID

   3. Biometric Signal Support (referencing FIDO2/Passkeys [FIDO2]
      and liveness detection best practices [ISO30107]):
      ```json
      {
        "biometric_binding": {
          "type": "heartbeat_signature|voice_print|behavioral|facial_liveness",
          "template_hash": "sha256:hash-of-biometric-template",
          "capture_timestamp": 1712345678,
          "liveness_proof": {
            "type": "active|passive|hybrid",
            "challenge_response": "base64-response",
            "confidence_score": 0.99,
            "spoofing_resistance": "high"
          },
          "verifier": "https://biometric-verifier.example",
          "privacy_mode": "zero_knowledge|template_only"
        }
      }
      ```

      Biometric Requirements:
      - Liveness detection MUST resist presentation attacks
      - Template storage SHOULD use secure enclave
      - Zero-knowledge proofs MAY protect raw biometric data
      - Multi-modal biometrics RECOMMENDED for high-assurance

   4. Multi-Factor Combination (maximum level):
      ```json
      {
        "hardware_proof": {
          "type": "maximum",
          "binding_level": "maximum",
          "factors": [
            {
              "type": "tee",
              "evidence": {
                "tee_type": "Intel-TDX",
                "mr_td": "hex-measurement",
                "report_data": "vdf-challenge-binding"
              },
              "weight": 0.4
            },
            {
              "type": "vdf",
              "proof": {
                "scheme": "pietrzak",
                "difficulty": 1000000,
                "output": "base64-output",
                "proof": "base64-proof"
              },
              "weight": 0.3
            },
            {
              "type": "biometric",
              "data": {
                "type": "facial_liveness",
                "template_hash": "sha256:hash",
                "liveness_proof": {...}
              },
              "weight": 0.3
            }
          ],
          "combined_attestation": "base64-multi-factor-attestation",
          "threshold": 0.9
        }
      }
      ```

      Multi-Factor Requirements:
      - Each factor cryptographically bound to receipt ID
      - Combined score MUST meet configured threshold
      - Failure of any single factor MAY be compensated by others
      - All factor evidence included in Tier 2 contextual_evidence

   5. Backward Compatibility:
      - enhanced level backward compatible with standard (verifiers
        MAY ignore VDF, validate TEE only)
      - maximum level requires enhanced verifier, but receipts
        parsable by base implementations (unknown fields ignored per
        JSON spec)

   Security Analysis:
   - VDF prevents real-time forgery attacks by enforcing sequential
     computation delay
   - Biometric binding provides human-in-the-loop proof
   - Multi-factor design prevents single-point-of-failure
   - Comparable to PoP physical binding strength when maximum level
     enabled

   Privacy Considerations:
   - Biometric templates hashed, raw data never stored in receipt
   - Zero-knowledge proofs MAY conceal biometric details
   - Liveness detection prevents replay of biometric data
   - Tier 3 protections apply to biometric evidence

