Appendix I.  Dispute Resolution Workflow Examples

I.1.  Scenario: Platform Compromise Suspected

   Timeline:
   T0: $Judge receipt R1 generated in TEE environment
   T1: $Delegate receipt R2 generated (normal operation)
   T2: dual mode verification detects conflict
       - open mode: VALID (cryptographic proof intact)
       - platform mode: INVALID (signature verification fails)
       - State: DISPUTED_FROZEN, chain frozen

   T3: Security team investigates, confirms platform key
       compromise, but cryptographic proofs intact

   T4: Governance committee issues $Resolve receipt R3:
       ```json
       {
         "event_type": "Resolve",
         "target_dispute_receipt": "R2-id",
         "resolution_type": "RESOLVED_CONTINUE",
         "resolution_statement": "Platform key compromised but
           cryptographic chain intact per open verification.
           Chain authorized to continue with enhanced monitoring.",
         "governance_signatures": ["sig1", "sig2", "sig3"]
       }
       ```

   T5: Chain unfreezes, R2 marked "verified_with_resolution",
       subsequent operations proceed normally

I.2.  Scenario: Deep Chain Invalidation

   Timeline:
   T0-T10: 10-level delegation chain established
   T11: dual mode detects conflict at level 7, investigation
        reveals systematic tampering in sub-delegation

   T12: Governance issues $Resolve with RESOLVED_INVALID:
       - Receipts R7-R10 marked "invalid"
       - Chain MUST be re-initiated from R6 (last known good)
       - New $Delegate from R6 to replacement actors

I.3.  Automated Recovery Example

   T0: $Judge in high-latency environment
   T1: dual mode verification
       - platform mode: VALID (< 10ms)
       - open mode: TIMEOUT (> 100ms, network issue)
   T2: Auto-retry open mode (attempt 1/3)
   T3: Auto-retry open mode (attempt 2/3)
   T4: Open mode succeeds on 3rd attempt
   T5: Auto-resolved to VALID with "auto_resolved" flag and
       diagnostic log: "open_mode_retry_succeeded"


